ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-1 The flight departed Dekalb-Peachtree Airport, moments later the pilot radioed that the airplane had a landing gear problem, and there was smoke in the cockpit. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-2 The pilot was instructed to enter visual traffic for runway 2R. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-3 Once the airplane was in the traffic pattern, the controller told the pilot that it appeared that the landing gear was extended, and cleared the flight to land. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-4 As the airplane neared touchdown the controller told the pilot that the landing gear was not locked and instructed the pilot to go-around. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-5 As the airplane flew by the control tower, smoke was seen coming from the airplane. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-6 As the pilot maneuvered the airplane for a landing on runway 27, the pilot was again instructed to go-around. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-7 Seconds later, the airplane touched down in a grassy area between the approach ends of runways 2L and 2R. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-8 Examination of the airplane disclosed that the airplane had sustained extensive fire damage to the floor area beneath the pilot's seat. 
ntsb3773txt-1-5-5-0-9 The examination revealed that a flex hydraulic fluid supply line was missing, and there had been electrical arcing in the immediate vicinity of the hot spot. 
